Former colleagues of the late Deputy Speaker of Lagos State House of Assembly, Adetoun Adediran, have visited her family in Surulere, Lagos State. The team was led by Minister of State for Health Olorunnimbe Mamora. Mamora described Adediran’s death as a shock, saying it was difficult to accept. “It is still difficult to accept, and still shocking even now. Perhaps it would have been different if we had hint of her being ill and hospitalised. But then we are human at the end of the day.   2023: ‘Zoning good, but competence better’     Council to go after debtors     Media firm unveils Lagos Show Podcast   “During her time in the House of Assembly, she was considered the right person for the deputy Speaker. She was very amiable, well loved by her colleagues, devoted herself to duty, and even after her tenure, she served the party in other capacities. We will miss her.” - Advertisement - Current Deputy Speaker Wasiu Eshinlokun-Sanni, on behalf of the Assembly, donated gifts to the deceased’s daughters. Adesola, one of the daughters, said: “I am very grateful to everyone that came here today to honour my mum. May the Almighty God honour you too.” The bother, Ademola Adediran, promised to nurture his sister’s children and help to accomplish their mother’s wishes for them. He appreciated the gift showered on them, and prayed for journey mercies for the visitors.